radiographic_examinations.findings: Radiograph demonstrating nonunion of the distal part of the humerus and loose hardware. There is no evidence of periosteal reaction.
radiographic_examinations.changes_over_time: Lateral radiograph of elbow thirteen months after total elbow arthroplasty showed evidence of loosening about the ulnar component.

radiographic_examinations.findings: Lateral radiograph of elbow following total elbow arthroplasty with placement of an intercalary tibial allograft.

radiographic_examinations.date: Thirteen months after the total elbow arthroplasty
radiographic_examinations.findings: Lateral radiograph showed an area of lucency surrounding the ulnar component.
